    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "There are no possible overflow from `SMOD` because `sgn(μₛ[0]) (|μₛ[0]| mod |μₛ[1]|)` is always in the range `(-2^{255}, 2^{255})` (the endpoints exclusive).  This is because `|μₛ[0]| mod |μₛ[1]|` is always smaller than `2^{255}`, which is because `|μₛ[1]|` is at most `2^{255}`, when `μₛ[1]` is the smallest signed 256-bit integer.\n",
